Police kill seven suspects, in a gang-related shootout, in Scottsville, Pietermaritzburg. Courtesy #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Police have killed seven suspects in a shootout at a house in Scottsville, Pietermaritzburg. One of the suspects is believed to be part of a group that escaped from custody earlier this year. READ: Harrismith protest: Woman's leg amputated after accident with police vehicle Police say some of those shot were responsible for a violent crime spree in various suburbs of Pietermaritzburg. No police officers were injured in the shootout.